    <text type="letter">
        <body> 
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_es.00318.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>Superintendent's Office.<ptr
                            target="loc.07229_n1"/><lb/>ASYLUM FOR THE INSANE<lb/>LONDON.<lb/>
                        ONTARIO<lb/>London, Ont.,</name><date when="1888-08-30" rend="right"
                            ><handShift rend="manuscript"/>30 Aug <handShift rend="printed"
                            />188<handShift rend="manuscript"/>8</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>I feel quite anxious about the "Complete Works"<ptr target="n4151"/> and would like
                much to hear from you how you will deal with that book. I think:
            <list>
            <item>1 The book should be first class in all aspects</item>
            <item>2 Price should be &#36;10.</item>
            <item>3 It should (every copy of it) be autograph</item>
            <item>4 Should contain a number of pictures</item>
            <item>5 Should be sold entirely by yourself</item>
            <item>6 A full advertisement of it should go in "N.B."<ptr target="n3999"/></item>
            </list>
            </p>
            <p>If you would tell Horace<ptr target="n4267"/> to write me your decision on each of
                these points you would relieve my mind very much</p>
            <p>There is nothing new or special here, all jogging on the old way.</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Your friend</salute>
                <signed rend="right">RM Bucke</signed>
            </closer>
